column5: Instead of going fishing this morning,I went up for breakfast with the parents. Been since last summer since I seen them due to covid. Sure was nice to visit again. While I was there,I got to feed the locals. My pop can walk out there as I said before, and feed them right from his hand. Me well, I was just lucky to see them and watch as I dropped off some feed. They knew I was not me pop,as they were leary and spooked very easy.  The slightest crack of my foot step and they backed off.  Pretty cool none the less.
Great looking herd.  Season opens in six months.
I don’t like to hand feed my dinner lol
It gets worse if you name them.
Weird thing about this property Glen. 4 years that I hunted it,we seen one doe. That is it. Winter comes and they they are.
